notesStmt.note: Third work, incipit f. 144v: Femina pessima, femina sordida, digna kathesis... in verse and prose, compiled from Pseudo-Hildebert and other sources.
Two leaves laid in have notes in a 16th-century[?] hand.

msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msItem.title: Sermones de tempore, sanctis et variis causis

supportDesc.extent: 249 leaves : 215 x 155 (168 x 115) mm. bound to 226 x 155 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 249; multiple schemes of contemporary foliation in ink, upper right recto; [1-249]; later foliation in ink, upper right recto.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a Gothic cursive script by several different hands.

decoDesc.decoNote: Red initials, some with penwork ornamentation (for example, f. 198r); rubricated capitals and underlining throughout; manicule (f. 234r).
Reused manuscript leaf pastedown, Inside front cover

binding.p: Contemporary stamped calf over wooden boards, with one clasp intact and remains of the second. Binding is cracking along both hinges. Front and back pastedowns are manuscript leaves from a gradual, with musical notation, on parchment.

origin.p: Written in Austria in the second half of the 15th century (Zacour-Hirsch).

history.provenance: Appears in Jacques Rosenthal's catalog 83 (1925), no. 11.
Sold at auction at Hauswedell, 5 May 1954, lot 13.
